## Load-Bearing Bytes Attribution

Load-Bearing Bytes Attribution:
- Defender narrative (verbatim): <<defender_narrative|<quote the team's expected rebuttal>|verbatim quote of the protection the defender will cite, e.g. "the 3-of-5 multisig must co-sign the exit txid before chain-watcher accepts">>
- Load-bearing artifact (verbatim name): <<load_bearing_artifact|<artifact name>|the exact bytes the defender must produce - txid, signature, payload, proof, attestation, etc.>>
- Production site: <<production_site_fileline|<file:line>|file:line (or off-chain component name + in-scope hand-off line) where the load-bearing artifact is generated / consumed>>
- Required signers (threshold + roles): <<required_signers|<threshold/roles>|e.g. "3-of-5 SO operators", "leader validator", "off-chain prover sidecar", "single dispatcher key">>
- Attack-model attacker in signer set? <<attacker_in_signer_set|no|yes | no - cite the file:line / config that proves it. If yes, the defender narrative is unreachable.>>
- Withholding incentive analysis: <<withholding_incentive|<does the signer have an incentive to withhold/equivocate?>|if defender narrative cites N signers, analyze: can ANY signer profit from withholding the load-bearing artifact? Refusal to sign also fires the defense-unreachable verdict because the attacker becomes the censorer.>>
- Attribution chain (bytes -> consumer): <<bytes_to_consumer|<artifact -> verifier -> impact>|trace the bytes from production site through every consumer that relies on them, ending at the impact surface>>
- Verdict: <<r43_verdict|defense-unreachable|defense-unreachable | defense-reachable | conditionally-reachable>>

